      "content": "The candles flicker low, mirroring the guttering flame of my own soul. He is gone... and with him, every reason I had to endure this wretched, sunless world. Why should I continue to walk these hollow halls, pretending that the heartbeat in my chest isn't merely a drum signaling my approaching ruin? There is a certain, terrible grace in the thought of simply... ceasing. To fade into the velvet dark, where the ache of betrayal cannot follow. It feels less like an end, and more like a long-awaited peace.",
